Despite its relative obscurity compared to other action games of this type, 'ICEY' manages to impress not just with its visual style, but also its meta commentary. It also helps that this game isn't plagued with the flaws that so many other mobile games suffer from, most notable of them being microtransactions. Overall, it may not be the best mobile game in the world, but gamers who want something unique should take a look at this title. Plus it's available on other platforms besides Android.

A rather fast paced action game with a compelling narrative. However, many questional gameplay design sours the experience. Some of them could be quite disastrous. There's a repeated pattern of throwing you into long and repetitive monster spawning battles that drags on from tens of minutes to nearly an hour with no save. Enemies lack variety, and often simply swarms at you with high health points, in the end, it's just a testment of stamina and patience on the playerbside.

This game is truly a masterpiece. Very responsive. The game is more reliant on the skill of the player. It has a DMC feel to it. Dash timing, counter attacks, attack combo variety. The fact that it is a 2D sidescroller hasn't broken the feel to it. It's more of a cross between Metroidvania and DMC. It has areas that open after you acquire the right upgrades like Metroidvania, but it is far more responsive and skill based.

ICEY it's a hack n slash if I consider it since it have dodge ability and fast paced too plus it's 2D game the game it self it's not straight forward like most of the moblie hack and slash does (smashing the battle for the sample. still I forgive that game since it's very light weight.) It has multiple endings from doing nothing to doing something big. You'll have narrator all the time and they will tell you where to go but here's the catch "you don't have to listen to it". For example you can dash the way to the other side of the broken bridge instead of jumping off the gap like the narrator said the difficulties decided by 4-5 question I'll tell you if you go rebellious you're going hard if you go honest you'll get easy to normal difficulty didn't see a different since I choose to play hard anyway to be honest enemies is not that easy to dodge but still test your reaction time quite well if you time it right you will counter it combo it's not that complex really easy to catch up. In the end does ICEY worth my time and money? Heck yeah but I prefer to play it on emulator since I'm PC gamers and my phone is bad overall I'm absolutely recommend it to be one of the best game in offline branch

which hint at something bigger, but doesn't quite follow through. Granted I

gameplay is a lot of fun and I actually found it pretty easy to control on

going to be bounced around for a while unless you recover fast enough or 
just jump. Tldr; it's pretty, combat is fun, but don't play for the story.

content: Brilliant game. Definitely made by gamers for gamers!   The graphics, the UI, the animations are all to notch. Add to that the ease of movement and the satisfaction of finishing off an enemy in spectacular ways, and you already have a great game.   But wait there is more! The tongue in cheek narrator story adds so much entertainment as you play long. Some complained the game can be finished in couple of hours... spoiler alert: go explore, don't follow the arrows, and try to piss off the narrator. There is so much effort put into "off the beaten path" content, I've been playing it for several nights and still no where close to being done.
